featured_reviews.review_id:
Mehdawan - Maner Sharif is a famous and ancient village of Patna.
The mosque's tall tower and three domes is a ancient mosque with beautiful carvings. Most beautiful is mosque in Maner and  surrounding area. those built by Nawab Syed Maulvi Athar Hussain Jafri (Advocate) in 1288 Hijri. He built many mosques. Athar Husain was born in 1224 Hijri and died in 1306, you were a very good hearted person. When you went from palankeen to Mauja Mehdawan to Chhapra, the Palankeen would pass on your own land. When you aspired to go for Haj  So whoever expressed his wish, he included it with him. In which thirty thousand rupees were spent.
Mehdawan has a glorious past. The original place of Ulma-e-Sadiqpur is Maulana Syed Ahmadullah took an active part in the first war of independence - he was punished with KALA PANI (KNOW AS CELLULAR JAIL) for revolt against the British and was sent to ANDAMAM & NICOBAR ISLAND. He died after suffering rigorous imprisonment. Sufisant, Maulvi, Writer, Poet, Doctor, Lawyer etc. Many dignity are related to Mehdawan. Such as- Last Sajjad Nashin of Khanqah Mehdawan Syed Shah Ramadan Ali Jafri Alzainbi,Nawab Syed Shah Athar Hussain Jafri,Qazi Furukh Hussain,Meer Syed Iftekhar Hussain,Meer Syed Ahmadullah,Nawab Maulvi Abdul Latif,Maulana Abdul Ghafar,Hakim Mohammad Sharif,kurban Ali,Dr Syed Ahsan Ahmad,Hafiz Salahuddin Nehal etc.
(Adv Syed Asif Ahmad)
Mehdawan Maner Sharif

MEHDAWAN (Near MANER-SHARIF /PATNA) has a  glorious past!/It is the native place of ULMA E SADIQPUR / They took active part in the first Freedom struggle (war of Indipendence). but they were brutely crushed by the BRITISH.Rular's/ They were sent to CellularJail.in INDAMAM & NECOBAR ISLAND(KALA-PANI) / Where from very few come back/ Among them MOLANA YAHYA ALI was died on 25/02/1882  on Rose Island  & MOLANA AHMADULLAH died on26/11/1889 ON HEVIPER ISLAND /Both were laid to rest in the soil of  INDAMAN & NECOBAR. MANY dignity  belongs to Mehdawan/Such as  MD SOHEB(CITY MAGISTRATE ) MOHAMMAD. MASOOD(CHIEF MECHANICAL ENGINEER) MANSOOR AHMAD(DIPLOMATE) & REGISTRAR AHMAD SAHEB/ MANZOOR NAZAR. featured_reviews.review_id:
Maner Sharif, is a satellite town in Patna Metropolitan Region, in the Patna district in the Indian state of Bihar. Maner Sharif lies 24 km west of Patna the capital of Bihar on National Highway 30 (India). It comes 8 km before Bihta while travelling from Patna to Ara-Buxar via NH30. The town has tombs of Sufi saints Makhdoom Yahya Maneri and Makhdoom Shah Daulat, known as Bari Dargah (the great shrine) and Chhoti Dargah (the small shrine). Maner is an important tourist area and tourism centre . The city's name is said to come from its status as a center of tourism.

This is Old drawing for build it.

featured_reviews.review_id: Ibrahim Khan mosque, Patna, Bihar. It was built by Ibrahim Khan in 1619 and is one of the finest Mughal architecture in Bihar. Located On the premises of Chhoti dargah of Maner Sharif amidst all the beautiful architecture, this mosque on the west side of the Makhdoom Shah Daulat's tomb will allure you with its stunning carvings on it's wall made of Chunar sandstone.
